{
  "doc_id": "1037",
  "text": "One of the many challenges that the project teams face is to determine how to measure the success of the end product and its construction process. This challenge is also known as the determination of a sustainability rating. Although there is still not a single global source for a sustainability building rating system [CITATION_1] , there have been many successful efforts at regional, national, and international levels [CITATION_2] . Two of the most popular and widely used rating systems are the Leadership in Energy and Environmental Leadership (LEED) developed by USGBC, and Building Research Establishment's Environmental Assessment Method (BREEAM).",
  "correct_citation": {
